title: DIARY-Emerging Markets Economic Events to Oct 30
text:
Oct 22 (Reuters) -
For other diaries, please see:
Top economic events
Government debt auctions
Political and general news events
Index of all diaries
Guide to economic indicators
** This Diary is filed daily ***
THURSDAY, OCTOBER 22 WASHINGTON - International Monetary Fund (IMF) Managing Director Christine Lagarde speaks about gender equality PARIS - International conference for the economic recovery and development of Mali: "Building an Emerging Mali". Speakers: French President Francois Hollande, Malian President Ibrahim Boubacar Keita and OECD Secretary-General Angel Gurria. STELLENBOSCH, South Africa - South African Reserve Bank Governor Lesetja Kganyago speaks at an economic conference - 0640 GMT. JAKARTA - World Bank issues its quarterly economic review for Indonesia - 0200 GMT. FRIDAY, OCTOBER 23 SEOUL - Bank of Korea Governor Lee Ju-yeol to attend an international conference co-hosted by the Bank of Korea and Yonsei University - 0000 GMT. PARIS - Czech National Bank board member Kamil Janacek to attend a conference on "Securitization: the way forward?". SUNDAY, OCTOBER 25 ABU DHABI - Summit on Global Agenda 2015 (to Oct. 27). MONDAY, OCTOBER 26 JERUSALEM - Bank of Israel announces interest rate decision - 1430 GMT.
TUESDAY, OCTOBER 27 MEXICO CITY - European Central Bank board member Benoit Coeure at Instituto Tecnologico Autonomo de Mexico (ITAM) - 2200 GMT. WEDNESDAY, OCTOBER 28 HELSINKI - OECD Secretary-General Angel Gurria and OECD Deputy Secretary-General Mari Kiviniemi speaks at the OECD Public Governance Ministerial Meeting. SEOUL - The Korea Institute of Finance will hold a seminar on its 2016 forecast - 0430 GMT. ANKARA - Central bank of Turkey releases quarterly inflation report - 0800 GMT. ANKARA - Central bank of Turkey to publish the minutes of October policy meeting - 1200 GMT.
THURSDAY, OCTOBER 29 LONDON - UK Finance Minister George Osborne meets Brazilian finance minister Joaquim Levy as a part of UK-Brazil Economic and Financial Dialogue. CHISINAU - Central bank of Moldova holds monetary policy committee meeting. MEXICO CITY - Central bank of Mexico announces interest rate decision - 1900 GMT.
FRIDAY, OCTOBER 30 MOSCOW - Central bank of Russia announces interest rate decision - 1100 GMT.
